{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492482","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492482"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:32:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:32:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1076"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1076","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1076"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.25,0.09,0.07,0.15,0.44]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1076"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"88378"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1076","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1076"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2019-11-13T08:16:48+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-03T15:42:23+10:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2024-10-29T16:24:02+10:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-23 08:20:33"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1076"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"72573"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"377"},{"type":"tags","id":"1501"},{"type":"tags","id":"4298"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8147"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"290"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11401"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17570"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30194"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44496"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44767"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45063"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"72573"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"88378","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/88378"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-week history of painful and reddened swelling of her right breast (Image). She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. Her general practitioner had given her a 10-day course of amoxicillin, but she has not noticed any change to the swelling. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. The right breast feels warm and there is no fluctuant area or discrete mass to be felt. The left breast and both axillae are normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Change antibiotic to clindamycin","Incision and drainage","Fluconazole ointment","MRI breasts","Ultrasound-guided biopsy"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with persistent breast inflammation not responding to antibiotics, raising concern for inflammatory breast cancer. While infection is common, failure to respond to appropriate antibiotics should prompt the concern that the underlying problem could be malignancy and investigations need to focus in this direction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUltrasound-guided biopsy\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate next step as it can identify and sample any suspicious areas, while also detecting any occult abscess if present. It is readily available and can be performed despite inflammation, unlike mammography which may be limited by breast tenderness and oedema.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChange antibiotic to clindamycin\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate as the lack of response to initial antibiotics suggests either resistant infection or non-infectious cause. Simply changing antibiotics without further investigation may delay diagnosis of underlying malignancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncision and drainage\u003C/strong\u003E would only be appropriate if there was a discrete abscess, which is not evident on examination. This could potentially complicate future imaging interpretation if performed unnecessarily.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFluconazole ointment\u003C/strong\u003E would not be appropriate as fungal infection is unlikely given the presentation. Fungal infections typically present with scaling and itching rather than breast warmth and swelling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMRI breasts\u003C/strong\u003E, while useful for evaluating extent of disease in confirmed inflammatory breast cancer, is not the most appropriate first investigation. It is less readily available than ultrasound and does not facilitate immediate biopsy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf ultrasound does not identify a lesion for biopsy, a skin punch biopsy should be performed. Once infection is excluded, further imaging with mammogram and MRI may be required for complete evaluation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ultrasound-guided biopsy is essential to exclude inflammatory breast cancer in cases of persistent breast inflammation not responding to antibiotics.","Inflammatory breast cancer can present with breast erythema and warmth, mimicking infection.","Initial antibiotic therapy without improvement should prompt urgent investigation rather than antibiotic change."],"references":["Menta A, Fouad TM, Lucci A, et al. Inflammatory Breast Cancer. Surg Clin N Am 2018; 98:787-800. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30005774/","Mamouch F, Berrada N, Aoully Z, et al. Inflammatory Breast Cancer: A Literature Review. World J Oncol. 2018; 9:129-35. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6279456/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"72573"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1076"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15320"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15320","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15320"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/cb33732a-0a2b-4b9d-8475-a321ce299499.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/cb33732a-0a2b-4b9d-8475-a321ce299499.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":600,"height":416}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"72573","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/72573"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-03T15:42:11+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-03T15:43:11+10:30","number":8,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":"2025-03-03T15:42:17+10:30","plagiarismScore":0,"plagiarismReportUrl":"https://emedici-copyleaks.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/plagiarism-report-1076-8.pdf?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=DO00QAKVE68N83EBLT2J%2F20250928%2Fsyd1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20250928T210221Z\u0026X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\u0026X-Amz-Expires=601200\u0026X-Amz-Signature=c980595969a614ebb1b46a3a0a5ff3235969309260213e8d5e5ef7305c64089a"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1076"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"88378"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data